The evidence with the title 'Medicaid is out of control. Here's how to fix it. - The Washington Post ' says Mar 19, 2017  ... The federal government could cover long - term care costs while states would assume all costs for children and younger adults. ... Children or young adults , they account for only one-third of costs. The elderly and disabled constitute the other one-quarter of recipients, but they represent two-thirds of costs. 
